The Balkans, also known as the Balkan Peninsula, is a region in southeastern Europe that includes several countries. Here are the countries commonly considered part of the Balkans:

    Albania
    Bosnia and Herzegovina
    Bulgaria
    Croatia
    Greece
    Kosovo*
    Montenegro
    North Macedonia
    Romania*
    Serbia
    Slovenia*

*Note: Romania and Slovenia are not always considered part of the Balkans, as they are not geographically located on the Balkan Peninsula, but they are sometimes included due to historical, cultural, and political ties with other Balkan countries. Additionally, Kosovo is a disputed territory with a partially recognized independence.
